    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES43-5 AND ES53-5 - REASSEMBLY
        - SHIFT KNOB INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SHIFT KNOB INSTALLATION</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1300997">Figure 95</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1300997" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300995" filename="../figg13/G1300995.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 95. Shift Knob</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BEZEL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. LOCK WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. FLAT WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SHIFT KNOB</callout1>
                <callout1>6. ROLL PIN</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the .125" diameter roll pin into the hole in the shift lever so that approximately
                1/8" of roll pin sticks out on each side of the lever.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the shift knob onto the lever so that the roll pin fits into the slots on the shift
                knob. Please remember that the part number and the external boss on the tower casting are on the
                passenger side of the vehicle.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the flat washer and then the lock washer over the threaded portion of the shift
                lever.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the nut and tighten as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s13009_30.xml" xrefid="hl1300903">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1300903"/>
                </hotlnk>
                . DO NOT OVER TIGHTEN NUT.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check to see that knob is tight by twisting assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bezel into the knob assembly. Care must be taken during assembly so that the
                paint on the back is not scraped off. Installation of the bezel is best performed with your hands by
                first placing the front or large side of the bezel into the knob. Next push forward and down until the
                bezel snaps into place.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
